WASHINGTON – The House voted 245-182 Tuesday to block President Donald Trump's declaration of a national emergency along the southern border, but Democrats didn’t win enough support from Republicans to overcome Trump’s threatened veto.
Vice President Mike Pence and legal experts discussed the emergency declaration with Republican senators during their weekly caucus lunch Tuesday.
As the resolution moves to the Senate, here's what you need to know:Which Senate Republicans have said they’ll support the measure?
The national emergency has been controversial for Republicans, many of whom warned the president his move could set a bad precedent.
